# Fractional Knapsack

## Problem

In Fractional Knapsack, objects can be divided into fractions.

The goal is to maximize total profit while keeping total weight within the knapsack capacity.

Objects are selected based on maximum profit/weight ratio.

---

# Algorithm / Pseudo Code

BEGIN

INPUT number of items n
INPUT weight and profit of each item
INPUT capacity W

COMPUTE profit/weight ratio for each item

SORT all items in decreasing order of ratio

INITIALIZE totalProfit = 0

FOR each item

    IF item weight <= W

        totalProfit = totalProfit + item profit

        W = W - item weight

    ELSE

        fraction = W / item weight

        totalProfit = totalProfit + (item profit * fraction)

        BREAK

    ENDIF

ENDFOR

PRINT totalProfit

END

---

# Time Complexity

| Case               | Complexity |
| ------------------ | ---------- |
| Best/Average/Worst | O(n log n) |

Sorting dominates the complexity.

---

# Space Complexity

O(n)
---

# Important Points

* Greedy algorithm.
* Items can be divided.
* Select items based on maximum profit/weight ratio.
* Gives optimal solution.
* Different from 0/1 Knapsack because fractions are allowed.
